sub_title: Helping companies unlock the power of customer interactions @Zendesk
summary:
Hi! I'm Nadia and I help companies streamline their operations in order to improve efficiency, collaboration and CX with Zendesk. 

Zendesk is a service-first CRM company that builds support, sales, and customer engagement software designed to foster better customer relationships by simplifying the complexity of business and make it easy for companies and customers to create connections.

From large enterprises to start-ups, we believe that powerful, innovative customer experience should be within reach for every company, no matter the size, industry or ambition. Zendesk serves more than 200k+ customers across hundreds of industries in over 30 languages.

Feel free to connect with me if you're curious to learn more about CX, conversational CRMs and Zendesk.

projects:
[{'title': 'Backstage: Global Music Industry', 'date': {'start': {'month': 12, 'day': None, 'year': 2015}, 'end': {'month': 5, 'day': None, 'year': 2016}}, 'description': "The project ‘Backstage: Global Music industry’, initiated by Föreningen Ekonomerna's International & Business Committee, is an event which aims to highlight the international business opportunities and the world behind the scenes of this exclusive industry. Some of the most experienced professionals from various areas of this industry were invited to give a lecture about the going-ons of the music industry.

I acted as the Project Manager and I was in charge of the whole process from the event initiation to the event evaluation. This included tasks such as planning, logistics, delivery, control and monitoring, and shutdown of the event. 

My work resulted in attracting big industry professionals as speakers such as the Managing Director of Sony Music Entertainment. I also managed to draw an audience of over 100 people through digital and personal marketing. The event that my project group initiated was so successful that the event still runs annually without my involvement.", 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Nadia', 'last_name': 'Humble', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Helping companies unlock the power of customer interactions @Zendesk'}]}, {'title': 'Stockholm European Career Tour', 'date': {'start': {'month': 10, 'day': None, 'year': 2015}, 'end': {'month': 3, 'day': None, 'year': 2016}}, 'description': 'Föreningen Ekonomerna, the Business Association at Stockholm University aims to build networks with worldwide partners to give the members an opportunity for an international career. Stockholm European Career Tour is a project arranged by the International Committee inside Föreningen Ekonomerna, which offers a trip to a new major European business city each year for both international and Swedish students in order to learn about different international career opportunities and to experience different cultural and economic settings. 

I acted as the Marketing Manager and Student Coordinator. My main task was to attract and inform students about the trip as well as coordinating the group before and during the trip, and organised team-building events prior to the trip. 

My work resulted in attracting the most ambitious students and giving them the opportunity to meet with global organisations such as Google, AT&T and the European Parliament in Brussels. My organisation and teambuilding led to a very tight-knit group that thoroughly enjoyed the tour.
